	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002396_0001"/><!--pb/@n='90r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName> 48 Euston Square</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">13 August 
<lb/>1865</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p><choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he payments which 
<lb/>you will oblige me 
<lb/>by making for <persName>Agnes</persName>
<lb/>are as follows:</p>
<lb/><p>One hundred &amp; twenty 
<lb/>pounds a year to 
<lb/><persName>Madame Hocédé</persName>, 
<lb/>and probably the best 
<lb/>way of doing it would 
<lb/>be for an arrangement 
<lb/>to be made in <placeName>Paris</placeName>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002396_0002"/><!--pb/@n='90v'-->
<lb/>by which she could draw 
<lb/>it quarterly - and also 
<lb/>one Pound a month 
<lb/>as pocket money 
<lb/>for <persName>Agnes</persName><reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>A sum will also 
<lb/>be required for 
<lb/>Music &amp; German 
<lb/>masters and for 
<lb/>washing, and this 
<lb/><persName>Agnes</persName> will 
<w>ascer-<lb break="no"/>tain</w> and give you 
<lb/>information<reg>.</reg></p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002396_0003"/><!--pb/@n='91r'-->
<lb/><p>She has clothing 
<lb/>enough to last till 
<lb/>she goes out of 
<lb/>mourning and 
<lb/>then she will consult 
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi> Murray</persName> as to 
<lb/>what dresses she 
<lb/>may need, and 
<lb/>you will be good 
<lb/>enough to take 
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi> Murray's</persName> opinion 
<lb/>as sufficient 
<lb/>authority for the 
<lb/>amount necessary 
<lb/>to be spent in dress.</p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002396_0004"/><!--pb/@n='91v'-->
<lb/><p>In any question that 
<lb/>might arise you 
<lb/>will find <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Oswell's</persName>
<lb/>judgment with your 
<lb/>own sufficient for 
<lb/>guidance: <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Young's</persName>
<lb/>opinion will always 
<lb/>be reasonable and 
<lb/>of value. But in all 
<lb/>cases I am sure that 
<lb/>you will act for the 
<lb/>best or what at the 
<lb/>time seems to be so and 
<lb/>for that I shall be 
<lb/>satisfied and thankful 
<lb/>whatever may be the 
<lb/>result<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
			
